title: T20 Cricket World Cup | adidas x BCCI
description:
Continuing their unwavering support for team India, adidas unveiled the 'You Got This' campaign, aiming to foster a positive mindset for cricketers gearing up for ICC Men‚Äôs T20 World Cup. 

With this campaign adidas aims to encourage each one of them to reinvigorate their love for cricket and wave goodbye to pressure arising from the nation‚Äôs expectations of a win. Setting the stage for the much-awaited tournament, ‚ÄòYou Got This‚Äô awakens a sense of optimism and self-belief in team India. 

Set against the song, ‚ÄòUnder Pressure‚Äô by Queen & David Bowie, the ‚ÄòYou Got This‚Äô film delves into the intense pressure experienced by the team before every match. 

Featuring prominent Indian team players including Rohit Sharma, Virat Kohli, Hardik Pandya, Shubman Gill, Mohammed Siraj, Kuldeep Yadav and Ravindra Jadeja, the film captures every emotion that a cricketer feels before the game. 

Further, showcasing the backyard mindset which showcases the individual passion and love for the game in itself that helps each cricketer to rise above and play with joy and total freedom.

description:
Every year we hop across Pandals and different Pujos with a chilled bottle of Coke in our hand. Often this bottle of Coke doubles up as a conversation starter and leads to new friendships. It accompanies us on our journey of pandal hopping and feasting throughout the festival. This film traces that cherished journey across the festival where we unlock memories and create new ones as Coke quenches the thirst to celebrate Pujo right up to the very last drop.

title: Felix Baumgartner's supersonic freefall from 128k' - Mission Highlights
description:
¬ª Jump into more adrenaline filled aerial action: http://win.gs/MoreAerial
After flying to an altitude of 39,045 meters (128,100 feet) in a helium-filled balloon, Felix Baumgartner completed a record breaking jump for the ages from the edge of space, exactly 65 years after Chuck Yeager first broke the sound barrier flying in an experimental rocket-powered airplane. Felix reached a maximum of speed of 1,357.6 km/h or 843.6 mph(Mach 1.25) through the near vacuum of the stratosphere before being slowed by the atmosphere later during his 4:20 minute long freefall. The 43-year-old Austrian skydiving expert also broke two other world records (highest freefall, highest manned balloon flight), leaving the one for the longest freefall to project mentor Col. Joe Kittinger.

Song: http://smarturl.it/tafreespacedout

Watch the Full Recap: http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dOoHArAzdug

title: Driver-Partners: Meet Shafiul Toronto | Uber
description:
Shafiul‚Äôs story:
Finding and securing meaningful work can be difficult under the best of circumstances, and doing so often becomes extraordinarily challenging for those who are hearing impaired or lack hearing completely. In fact, the deaf and hard-of-hearing community faces a 70% unemployment and underemployment rate in the U.S. Although The Americans with Disabilities Act requires employers to accommodate a qualified applicant or employee‚Äôs known disability, those living with one can attest to the barriers they face as a result. 

Shafiul had a particularly difficult time finding work as a deaf person before partnering with Uber. He applied to numerous jobs, even to be a taxi driver, and was turned down time and time again. The employers he had met with viewed his lack of hearing as a problem that would be too expensive or challenging to manage. Due to the difficulty he had finding a means to earn money and the discrimination he faced, Shafiul especially values his partnership with Uber and appreciates that Uber sees him as what he is: an able individual. Like many drivers who choose to use Uber, Shafiul enjoys the flexibility and freedom the platform allows, as he is able to earn money driving and also make time for family and travel.  

Shafiul is a proud Canadian and has been driving with Uber for a year at this time. He hopes that his riders will leave his car knowing that deaf people are just as capable for work as anyone else.

Learn how Uber supports driver-partners who are deaf or hard of hearing: https://accessibility.uber.com/#driver-partners-who-are-deaf-or-hard-of-hearing

title: Mufasa: The Lion King | Teaser Trailer
description:
A lion who would change our lives forever. #Mufasa: The Lion King, in theaters December 20.

‚ÄúMufasa: The Lion King‚Äù enlists Rafiki to relay the legend of Mufasa to young lion cub Kiara, daughter of Simba and Nala, with Timon and Pumbaa lending their signature schtick. Told in flashbacks, the story introduces Mufasa as an orphaned cub, lost and alone until he meets a sympathetic lion named Taka‚Äîthe heir to a royal bloodline. The chance meeting sets in motion an expansive journey of an extraordinary group of misfits searching for their destiny‚Äîtheir bonds will be tested as they work together to evade a threatening and deadly foe.  
 
New and returning cast members were called on to lend their voices to the film:
- Aaron Pierre as Mufasa
- Kelvin Harrison Jr. as Taka, a lion prince with a bright future who accepts Mufasa into his family as a brother
- Tiffany Boone as Sarabi
- Kagiso Lediga as Young Rafiki
- Preston Nyman as Zazu
- Mads Mikkelsen as Kiros, a formidable lion with big plans for his pride 
- Thandiwe Newton as Taka‚Äôs mother, Eshe
- Lennie James as Taka‚Äôs father, Obasi 
- Anika Noni Rose as Mufasa‚Äôs mother, Afia
- Keith David as Mufasa‚Äôs father, Masego
- John Kani as Rafiki
- Seth Rogen as Pumbaa
- Billy Eichner as Timon
- Donald Glover as Simba
- Introducing Blue Ivy Carter as Kiara, daughter of King Simba and Queen Nala
- And Beyonc√© Knowles-Carter as Nala
 
Additional casting includes Braelyn Rankins, Theo Somolu, Folake Olowofoyeku, Joanna Jones, Thuso Mbedu, Sheila Atim, Abdul Salis and Dominique Jennings.

‚ÄúMufasa: The Lion King,‚Äù the new film coming to theaters Dec. 20 explores the unlikely rise of the beloved king of the Pride Lands. The film has an all-star roster of talent bringing new and fan-favorite characters to life‚Äîplus, celebrated award-winning songwriter Lin-Manuel Miranda is writing the film‚Äôs songs produced by Mark Mancina and Miranda, with additional music and performances by Lebo M. 
 
Said Miranda, ‚ÄúElton John. Tim Rice. Hans Zimmer. Lebo M. Mark Mancina. Beyonc√©, Labrinth, Ilya Salmanzadeh. Beau Black, Ford Riley, the incredible music team on ‚ÄòThe Lion Guard,‚Äô and so many musical contributors over the years. ‚ÄòThe Lion King‚Äô has an incredible musical legacy with music from some of the greatest songwriters around, and I'm humbled and proud to be a part of it. It's been a joy working alongside Barry Jenkins to bring Mufasa's story to life, and we can't wait for audiences to experience this film in theaters."
 
Blending live-action filmmaking techniques with photoreal computer-generated imagery, ‚ÄúMufasa: The Lion King‚Äù is directed by Barry Jenkins, produced by Adele Romanski & Mark Ceryak, and executive produced by Peter Tobyansen.

title: The Little Mermaid | Official Teaser Trailer
description:
Out of the sea, wish I could be... part of that world.

Disney's The Little Mermaid is coming to theaters May 26, 2023.

‚ÄúThe Little Mermaid,‚Äù visionary filmmaker Rob Marshall‚Äôs live-action reimagining of the studio‚Äôs Oscar¬Æ-winning animated musical classic, opens exclusively in theaters nationwide May 26, 2023. ‚ÄúThe Little Mermaid‚Äù is the beloved story of Ariel, a beautiful and spirited young mermaid with a thirst for adventure. The youngest of King Triton‚Äôs daughters, and the most defiant, Ariel longs to find out more about the world beyond the sea, and while visiting the surface, falls for the dashing Prince Eric. While mermaids are forbidden to interact with humans, Ariel must follow her heart. She makes a deal with the evil sea witch, Ursula, which gives her a chance to experience life on land, but ultimately places her life ‚Äì and her father‚Äôs crown ‚Äì in jeopardy. 

The film stars singer and actress Halle Bailey (‚Äúgrown-ish‚Äù) as Ariel; Tony Award¬Æ winner Daveed Diggs (‚ÄúHamilton,‚Äù ‚ÄúSnowpiercer‚Äù) as the voice of Sebastian; Jacob Tremblay (‚ÄúLuca,‚Äù ‚ÄúRoom‚Äù) as the voice of Flounder; Awkwafina (‚ÄúRaya and the Last Dragon‚Äù) as the voice of Scuttle; Jonah Hauer-King (‚ÄúA Dog‚Äôs Way Home‚Äù) as Prince Eric; Art Malik (‚ÄúHomeland‚Äù) as Sir Grimsby; Noma Dumezweni (‚ÄúMary Poppins Returns‚Äù) as Queen Selina; with Oscar¬Æ winner Javier Bardem (‚ÄúNo Country for Old Men,‚Äù ‚ÄúBeing the Ricardos‚Äù) as King Triton; and two-time Academy Award¬Æ nominee Melissa McCarthy (‚ÄúCan You Ever Forgive Me?‚Äù ‚ÄúBridesmaids‚Äù) as Ursula.      

‚ÄúThe Little Mermaid‚Äù is directed by Oscar¬Æ nominee Rob Marshall (‚ÄúChicago,‚Äù ‚ÄúMary Poppins Returns‚Äù), and written by two-time Oscar nominee David Magee (‚ÄúLife of Pi,‚Äù ‚ÄúFinding Neverland‚Äù), with a live-action story adaptation by David Magee, Rob Marshall, and two-time Emmy winner John DeLuca (‚ÄúTony Bennett: An American Classic‚Äù), based on the short story by Hans Christian Andersen, and the Disney animated film by Ron Clements and John Musker. The film is produced by two-time Emmy¬Æ winner Marc Platt (‚ÄúJesus Christ Superstar Live in Concert,‚Äù ‚ÄúGrease Live!‚Äù), three-time Tony Award¬Æ winner Lin-Manuel Miranda (‚ÄúHamilton,‚Äù ‚ÄúIn the Heights‚Äù), Rob Marshall, and John DeLuca, with Jeffrey Silver (‚ÄúThe Lion King‚Äù) serving as executive producer. The score is by multiple Academy Award¬Æ winner Alan Menken (‚ÄúBeauty and the Beast,‚Äù ‚ÄúAladdin‚Äù), who won two Oscars¬Æ for the music in the animated version of ‚ÄúThe Little Mermaid,‚Äù with music supervised and produced by Mike Higham (‚ÄúMary Poppins Returns,‚Äù ‚ÄúInto the Woods‚Äù). Music is by Alan Menken, lyrics are by Howard Ashman and new lyrics are by Lin-Manuel Miranda.

title: Disney's Cruella | Official Trailer
description:
Brilliant. Bad. A little bit mad. May 2021.

Get tickets to experience Disney‚Äôs #Cruella in theaters or pre-order on #DisneyPlus with Premier Access May 28 (additional fee required).
Get Tickets: http://bit.ly/TixCruella

Academy Award¬Æ winner Emma Stone (‚ÄúLa La Land‚Äù) stars in Disney‚Äôs ‚ÄúCruella,‚Äù an all-new live-action feature film about the rebellious early days of one of cinemas most notorious ‚Äì and notoriously fashionable ‚Äì villains, the legendary Cruella de Vil. ‚ÄúCruella,‚Äù which is set in 1970s London amidst the punk rock revolution, follows a young grifter named Estella, a clever and creative girl determined to make a name for herself with her designs. She befriends a pair of young thieves who appreciate her appetite for mischief, and together they are able to build a life for themselves on the London streets. One day, Estella‚Äôs flair for fashion catches the eye of the Baroness von Hellman, a fashion legend who is devastatingly chic and terrifyingly haute, played by two-time Oscar¬Æ winner Emma Thompson (‚ÄúHowards End,‚Äù ‚ÄúSense & Sensibility‚Äù). But their relationship sets in motion a course of events and revelations that will cause Estella to embrace her wicked side and become the raucous, fashionable and revenge-bent Cruella.
¬†
Disney‚Äôs ‚ÄúCruella‚Äù is directed by Craig Gillespie (‚ÄúI Tonya‚Äù) from a screenplay by Dana Fox and Tony McNamara, story by Aline Brosh McKenna and Kelly Marcel & Steve Zissis. It was produced by Andrew Gunn (‚ÄúFreaky Friday‚Äù), Marc Platt (‚ÄúMary Poppins Returns‚Äù) and Kristin Burr (‚ÄúChristopher Robin‚Äù), with Emma Stone, Michelle Wright, Jared LeBoff and Glenn Close serving as executive producers. Two-time Oscar¬Æ- winning costume designer Jenny Beavan (‚ÄúMad Max: Fury Road,‚Äù ‚ÄúA Room with a View‚Äù) creates the dazzling and imaginative costumes, which take on a life of their own.

title: Intentionally Shattering Wafers Inside The Fab | Intel
description:
Meet Ryan Parrott, Packaging Engineer at Intel. His job is to design and test the custom packaging solutions used to ship silicon wafers all over the world. In order to learn which solutions work, Ryan has got to push expensive wafers potentially containing thousands of processors to their breaking points. 
 
The packaging used to ship wafers is called a Front-Opening Shipping Box, or FOSB. Each of these specially-designed boxes contain 25 glass-like, silicon wafers totaling $250,000 to multi-million US dollars per box depending on product. Each wafer is incredibly fragile, and it's Ryan's job to insure that each FOSB makes it to its destination with all wafers intact. 
 
Check out Ryan's story, and stay tuned for more stories "Inside the Fab" at Intel.

title: The Most Sophisticated Manufacturing Process In The World  Inside The Fab | Intel
description:
Meet John Breseke, Director of Manufacturing IT at Intel whose job it is to manage the IT and automation of arguably the most automated and sophisticated manufacturing process in the world.
 
 Boxes of twenty-five total, 12 inch in diameter silicon wafers have to be transported within Intel manufacturing facilities around the world using the AMHS (automated material handling system). John and his team have to track and manage the workflow of products throughout the AMHS at any given point in order to enable manufacturing within fabrication facilities, keeping projects on time and on budget.

title: Silicon Manufacturing & The Perfect Wafer Inside The Fab | Intel
description:
Meet Dave Pivin, a Failure Analyst Engineer at Intel whose job it is to continuously push towards the production of a perfect silicon wafer. As Dave puts it, it's like "Looking in a million haystacks for a single needle". 
 
As silicon wafer production moves smaller and smaller, from 22 nanometer to 14 nanometer, imperfections in production are tough to see even with high-powered microscopes. Dave and his team of fellow scientists are charged with identifying the causes of these nearly invisible defects. 
 
Check out Dave's story, and stay tuned for more stories "Inside the Fab" at Intel.

title: Mentra: The future of work is neurodiverse
description:
Neurodivergent professionals often face significant obstacles in finding a supportive workplace environment needed for career growth and success. Mentra is a groundbreaking job platform founded by Jhillika Kumar and Connor Reinhardt to address these challenges. 

Powered by Microsoft AI, Mentra streamlines the job search process for neurodivergent candidates by using a gamified environment where they can express their preferred accommodations and showcase their specific talents. Through AI recommendations, Mentra connects these candidates with potential employers, aiming to eliminate barriers for companies and tap into the diverse talent pool of neurodiverse individuals. Mentra seeks to promote the potential of neurodiverse individuals and foster inclusivity in the workplace.

Get the full story on Unlocked: https://unlocked.microsoft.com/mentra-neuroinclusion/
